<title>SOUTH AFRICA: ADMIRAL RENEWS CAUTIONARY ON BUY TALKS.</title>
<headline>ADMIRAL RENEWS CAUTIONARY ON BUY TALKS.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-08-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Africa's Admiral Leisure World Ltd on Friday renewed earlier cautionaries in which it said it was in talks to buy an international company which could have an impact on its share price.</p>
<p>The company said on February 27 if the acquisition was successful, it would be funded partly by the issue of new shares and partly out of borrowings.</p>
<p>Shareholders were advised to continue to exercise caution in their sharedealings until a further announcement is made.</p>
<p>Admiral last renewed the cautionary on July 18.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom 27 11 482 1003</p>
